        "timestamp": "2017-05-10 19:23:06.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n\nWe want to be careful to keep the implementation code separate from the data objects that are created when a directed graph is compiled.  If we made this change, then any time we make a fix to the implementation code, we would need to recompile our directed graphs.  That's why this functionality is in the \"resolver\" classes today rather than in the SvcLogicExpression class and its children.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "c81a2b6bb3f952618f4e2eefe5122ef114b8a9a5",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 35,
          "name": "Gary Wu",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gary.wu@gmail.com",
          "username": "gwu"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-05-10 19:35:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAh, thanks for the explanation.  It may be worthwhile to document this rationale somewhere so that others don't run into the same thing later.\n\nAny ideas what happens today if there is a mismatch between the compiled DG objects and the running code in SDNC?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
